    "Here's the completed solution:",
    "",
    "import java.util.*;",
    "import java.lang.*;",
    "",
    "class Solution {",
    "    public boolean isPalindrome(String string) {",
    "        int i = 0;",
    "        int j = string.length() - 1;",
    "        while (i < j) {",
    "            if (string.charAt(i) != string.charAt(j)) {",
    "                return false;",
    "            }",
    "            i++;",
    "            j--;",
    "        }",
    "        return true;",
    "    }",
    "",
    "    public String makePalindrome(String string) {",
    "        if (string.isEmpty()) return \"\";",
    "",
    "        // Find the longest palindromic suffix",
    "        for (int i = 0; i < string.length(); i++) {",
    "            String suffix = string.substring(i);",
    "            if (isPalindrome(suffix)) {",
    "                // Reverse the prefix that comes before the palindromic suffix",
    "                String prefix = string.substring(0, i);",
    "                String reversedPrefix = new StringBuilder(prefix).reverse().toString();",
    "                return string + reversedPrefix;",
    "            }",
    "        }",
    "",
    "        return string;",
    "    }",
    "}",
    "",
    "How it works:",
    "- Iterate through the string, trying each possible suffix (i to end)",
    "- Find the longest palindromic suffix (first match from the left)",
    "- Take the prefix before that suffix, reverse it, and append it to the original string",
    "",
    "Example: \"cat\" -> suffix \"t\" is palindrome, prefix \"ca\" reversed = \"ac\", result = \"catac\""
  ],
